 me for like 1k, taking me to about 800 HP? I dunno something like that.  He speared me again and I zoned.  I fought him yesterday in PoD and it happened again.    Any tips on SK PVP?    When I get 62+ its not gonna matter when they just DT me but still.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=legolos>Legolos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 526<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 10:47 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz vs. SK</span><hr size=1> Well, playing on a PvP server so I assume your resists are WAY WAY up there.  But the Spear nukes he was using is diseased based.  So just make sure you have high resists for that.  If you see him activate his /disc for harm touch, it will also be a diseased base nuke (-200 resist adjust).  Othwise his normal HT is magic (-200 adjust).   You are prob not going to resist the HT so your best bet will be to resist his Spears so your epic can eat the HT.  Also keep Spell Shield up as it will null his spears and life taps if they land.   If you picking on him in a area where you can't run around you aren't going to do well at your level.  Your options on nukes are limited.  Best bet is to catch him un-aware,  hide behind a zone object that he will have to spend time looking for you.  Annul him atleast 2 times then pick a corner and start chaining nukes.  If it gets bad just shadow step / gate to your bind point re-epic and go again.  After he blows that HT he's not as tough, and they freak out when they gota smack on you for about 5 rounds to actually do damage to you as you are chaining him from a corner. <p><br><center><b>Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21704">Legolos</a> Spellbynder |  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21727">Uggliey</a> Bugger<br>LvL 65 Arcanist | LvL 56 Revenant<br>
Of the <a href="http://www.prexuseq.com">Prexus</a> Server</b><br><img src="http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-4/165760/VHFYFZCUIUHSHVKQZXJR-Crit.jpg" width=223 height=15><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rallaielfyrefingers>Rallaiel Fyrefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 12:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz vs. SK</span><hr size=1> Why not toss Spellshield on top of your epic? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pickkpockket999>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 1:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz vs. SK</span><hr size=1> Get a few levels so you are at least 63ish.<br>
<br>
-Put on spellshield + Rune of your choice.<br>
-Buy a 100k horse as the SK will most likely have his AA horse.<br>
-Lure of Ro + Lure Rain when he stops to tap, lead off with a dispell.<br>
-When rune comes off yonder away and re-apply.<br>
-Rinse and repeat<br>
